In 2008â09, '''[[FC Barcelona|Futbol Club Barcelona]]''' started a new era with a new manager, former player and [[FC Barcelona AtlÃ¨tic]] manager [[Josep Guardiola]], who led the team to the first [[The Treble|Treble]] in Spanish football history. After selling off high-profiled players such as [[Deco]] and [[Ronaldinho]], Barcelona played brilliant football throughout the season, winning the [[Copa del Rey]], [[La Liga]], and the [[UEFA Champions League]], due to a large contribution from its [[cantera]]no players from [[La Masia]]. Guardiola adopted a modern day equivalent of [[Total Football]] and led the team to one of the best seasons ever had in European football.

